  19. The HCL Company is manufacturing the computers; the company is having the fixed stock size to hold the manufactured computers. The client can place the order if stock is not empty and company cannot manufacture the computers if the stock size full. Develop an application to handle the situation.

    Program :


    include<stdio.h> include<stdlib.h>

    int mutex=1,full=0,empty=3,x=0; int main()

    D

    int n;

    void producer(); void consumer(); int wait(int);

    int signal(int);

    printf("\n1.To Manufacture the Computer\n2.To Order the Computer\n3.Exit"); while(1)

    D

    printf("\nEnter your choice:"); scanf("%d",&n);

    switch(n) D

    case 1: if((mutex==1)&&(empty!=0)) producer();

    else

    printf("Stock are full!!"); break;

    case 2: if((mutex==1)&&(full!=0)) consumer();

    else

    printf("Stocks are empty!!"); break;

    case 3: exit(0); break;

    }

    }

    return 0;

    }


    int wait(int s) D

    return (--s);

    }

    int signal(int s) D

    return(++s);

    }


    void producer() D

    mutex=wait(mutex); full=signal(full); empty=wait(empty); x++;

    printf("\nManufactured the Computer %d",x); mutex=signal(mutex);

    }

    void consumer() D

    mutex=wait(mutex); full=wait(full); empty=signal(empty);

    printf("\nOrdered the Computer %d",x); x--;

    mutex=signal(mutex);

    }

    Output:

  20. Five persons are in a queue to book railway tickets. There is only one counter and all of them arrived at 9.30 AM. The counter will be open by

    10.00 AM. The processing time for each person to book the tickets are 10 minutes, 20 minutes, 5 minutes, 7 minutes and 13 minutes respectively. Identify the scheduling algorithm and write a C program for the same.


    (FIFO)

    Program :


    include <stdio.h> typedef struct fcfs D

    int process; int burst; int arrival; int tat;

    int wt;

    }fcfs;

    int sort(fcfs [], int); int main()

    D

    int n, i, temp = 0, AvTat = 0, AvWt = 0;


    printf ("Enter the number of processes: "); scanf ("%d", &n);

    fcfs arr[n]; int tct[n];

    for (i = 0; i < n; i++) D

    arr[i].process = i;

    printf ("Enter the process %d data\n", arr[i].process); printf ("Enter CPU Burst: ");

    scanf ("%d", &(arr[i].burst)); printf ("Enter the arrival time: "); scanf ("%d", &(arr[i].arrival));

    }

    sort(arr, n);

    printf ("Process\t\tBurst Time\tArrival Time\tTurn Around Time\tWaiting Time\n");

    for (i = 0; i < n; i++) D

    tct[i] = temp + arr[i].burst; temp = tct[i];

    arr[i].tat = tct[i] - arr[i].arrival;

    arr[i].wt = arr[i].tat - arr[i].burst; AvTat = AvTat + arr[i].tat;

    AvWt = AvWt + arr[i].wt;

    printf ("%5d\t%15d\t\t%9d\t%12d\t%12d\n", arr[i].process, arr[i].burst, arr[i].arrival, arr[i].tat, arr[i].wt);

    }

    printf ("Average Turn Around Time: %d\nAverage Waiting Time: %d\n", AvTat / n, AvWt / n);

    return 0;

    }

    int sort(fcfs arr[], int n) D

    int i, j; fcfs k;


    for (i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) D

    for (j = i + 1; j < n; j++) D

    if (arr[i].arrival > arr[j].arrival) D

    k = arr[i]; arr[i] = arr[j]; arr[j] = k;

    }

    }

    }

    return 0;

    }

Remember that all frames are initially empty, so your first unique pages will all cost one fault each.


    Program :


    include<stdio.h>

    int findLRU(int time[], int n)D

    int i, minimum = time[0], pos = 0; for(i = 1; i < n; ++i)D

    if(time[i] < minimum)D minimum = time[i]; pos = i;

    }

    }

    return pos;

    }

    int main() D

    int no_of_frames, no_of_pages, frames[10], pages[30], counter = 0, time[10], flag1, flag2, i, j, pos, faults = 0;

    for(i = 0; i < no_of_pages; ++i)D scanf("%d", &pages[i]);

    }

    for(i = 0; i < no_of_frames; ++i)D frames[i] = -1;

    }

    for(i = 0; i < no_of_pages; ++i)D flag1 = flag2 = 0;

    time[j] = counter; flag1 = flag2 = 1; break;

    }

    }

    if(flag1 == 0)D

    for(j = 0; j < no_of_frames; ++j)D if(frames[j] == -1)D counter++;

    faults++;

    frames[j] = pages[i]; time[j] = counter; flag2 = 1;

    break;

    }

    }

    }

    if(flag2 == 0)D

    pos = findLRU(time, no_of_frames); counter++;

    faults++;

    frames[pos] = pages[i]; time[pos] = counter;

    }

  30. The Chip manufacturing Company is manufacturing the chips; the company is having the fixed stock size to hold the manufactured chips. The client can place the order if stock is not empty and company cannot manufacture the computers if the stock size full. Develop an application to handle the situation.


Program :


include<stdio.h> include<stdlib.h>

int mutex=1,full=0,empty=3,x=0; int main()

D

int n;

void producer(); void consumer(); int wait(int);

int signal(int);

printf("\n1.To Manufacture the Chips\n2.To Order the Chips\n3.Exit"); while(1)

D

printf("\nEnter your choice:"); scanf("%d",&n);

switch(n) D

case 1: if((mutex==1)&&(empty!=0)) producer();

else

printf("Stock are full!!"); break;

case 2: if((mutex==1)&&(full!=0)) consumer();

else

printf("Stocks are empty!!"); break;

case 3: exit(0); break;

}

}

return 0;

}


int wait(int s) D

return (--s);

}

int signal(int s) D

return(++s);

}


void producer() D

mutex=wait(mutex); full=signal(full); empty=wait(empty); x++;

printf("\nManufactured the Chips %d",x); mutex=signal(mutex);

}


void consumer() D

mutex=wait(mutex); full=wait(full); empty=signal(empty);

printf("\nOrdered the Chips %d",x); x--;

mutex=signal(mutex);

}
